m\",\"is_requested\":false,\"image\":{\"source\":\"/img/vendors/placeholder.png\",\"placeholder\":\"/img/vendors/placeholder.png\"}},\"is_public\":true,\"can_edit\":false}}}}",
  "steps": [
    "Prepare cryopreservation medium (10% dimethylsulfoxide in fetal bovine serum). undetermined, fetal bovine serum undetermined, dimethylsulfoxide",
    "Aliquot 0.2 mL cryopreservation medium into each cryovial. Larger volumes may be used with multiple biopsies. E.g. use 1 mL with 5-10 biopsies.",
    "Place one or more biopsies in each cryovial. Ensure that the biopsies are completely covered with cryopreservation medium. Add more to cover if necessary.",
    "Close cryovial, place in a Mr. Frosty, and freeze to -80C overnight. Any controlled rate cooling device that yields a decrease in temperature of 1C per minute can be used in place of a Mr. Frosty.",
    "For storage, place samples in a liquid nitrogen freezer until needed.",
    "Chill cryopreservation medium at 4C for at least 30 minutes. 00:30:00",
    "Put 5mL of cell culture medium of interest into a plate or well.",
    "Remove the cryovials from the liquid nitrogen freezer, but keep them on liquid nitrogen in a pan or other device for carrying liquid nitrogen until ready to thaw.",
    "Transfer cryovials to a 37C water bath and agitate until thawed.",
    "Transfer biopsies with forceps into 5 mL of room temperature culture medium.",
    "Incubate for 10 minutes at room temperature. 00:10:00",
    "Use biopsies as needed."
  ],
